"{\n  \"judgement\": \"The argument that religious beliefs can be a source of emotional harm, but also a source of personal conviction and meaning, is more nuanced than the blanket claim that religion inherently causes people to be judgmental and intolerant.\",\n  \"steering\": \"It's interesting to see how personal experiences with religion can shape perspectives on its impact. Maybe we can learn from each other's stories and try to understand where the other side is coming from?\"\n}"